### 1. Register a New Instructor
POST http://localhost:3000/instructor-api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Doee",
  "email": "jane.instructor@example.com",
  "password": "Password@123",
  "profileImageUrl": "https://example.com/avatar.png"
}

### 2. Login as Instructor (This sets the 'token' cookie)
POST http://localhost:3000/common-api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.instructor@example.com",
  "password": "Password@123"
}

### 3. Create a New Course (Requires being logged in)
# Replace instructor ID with your actual ID from the register/login response
POST http://localhost:3000/instructor-api/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "instructor": "69b8dc1842d4f339a37e2879",
  "title": "Mastering Node.js and S3",
  "category": "Web Development",
  "description": "A comprehensive guide to backend development with AWS S3 integration.",
  "lectures": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction to HLS",
      "duration": 300
    }
  ]
}

### 4. Upload and Transcode Video (MOCK TEST IDs)
# Ensure you have 'test.mp4' in the backend folder
POST http://localhost:3000/instructor-api/courses/69b8dc1842d4f339a37e287a/lectures/69b8dc18ffee92873bb216ee/video
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="video"; filename="test.mp4"
Content-Type: video/mp4

< ./test.mp4
--boundary--

### 5. Verify Authentication Status
GET http://localhost:3000/common-api/get-user

### 6. Logout
GET http://localhost:3000/common-api/logout
